<p>I am developing Javascript using Emacs.</p>  <p>I have a function that formats my Javascript code into <a href="http://standardjs.com/" rel="nofollow">Standard Style</a> on file save. My configuration looks like this:</p>  <pre><code>(add-hook 'js-mode-hook       (lambda ()         (add-hook 'before-save-hook 'standardfmt t t))) </code></pre>  <p>Unfortunately this hook has the side effect of applying to buffers using <code>json-mode</code> as well, since <code>json-mode</code> extends from <code>js-mode</code>.</p>  <p>Is there an easy way to exclude<code>json-mode</code> buffers from this hook?</p>